==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: greatest
<hw>greatest</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <ety>[<pos>superl.</pos> of
<er>great</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>not to be surpassed.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> top.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>largest in size of those under
consideration.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> biggest, largest.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>most of.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>highest in importance or degree or significance or
achievement; most eminent; <as>as, our <ex>greatest</ex>
statesmen</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> leading(prenominal), preeminent.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>highest in quality.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> sterling(prenominal), superlative.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Great-grandchild</ent>⟦br⟧
